results.title: Painting, acrylic painting, Baltic god, Patrimpas fertility god
results.description:
Painting – acrylic on canvas, horizontal format, 60x80 cm size, with thin black wooden frame. The frame can be easily changed if you have a better option for your interior. 
Exploring the themes of Baltic cultural heritage, ancient gods and and goddesses, as references I used archeological finds and written sources about Baltic cosmology and mythology. However, compositions are not straight forward illustrations of those sources, but more my own interpretations analysing the themes.

Patrimpas was ancient Prussian fertility, good harvest, rivers and war luck god. He was connected to spring fertility and was one of the three most important Prussian gods together with Perkūnas and Pikuolis. He gave happiness, plenty, calm, maturity to people. Took care of their cattle and grain.
